SIMPLE: juke
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Juke
<hw>Juke</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <ety>[from Scottish
<ets>jouk</ets> to bow.]</ety> <def>To bend the neck; to bow or duck the
head.</def> <altsp>[Written also <asp>jook</asp> and
<asp>jouk</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The money merchant was so proud of his trust that he went
<qex>juking</qex> and tossing of his head.</q> <rj><qau>L'
Estrange.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Juke</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Juke
<hw>Juke</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The neck of a bird.</def> <mark>[Prov.
Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Juke</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Juke
<hw>Juke</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <ety>[F. <ets>juc</ets> a roost, perch,
<ets>jucher</ets> to roost, to perch.]</ety> <def>To perch on anything,
as birds do.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Jukebox</ent>⟦br⟧
